For statistical purposes, the United States Census Bureau defined a [[census-designated place]] (CDP) for the 2000 census that roughly corresponds to the same area as the hamlet.

As of the [[census]] of 2010, there were 650 people, 264 households, and 148 families residing in the CDP. The population density was {{convert|97.0|PD/sqmi|PD/km2|sp=us|adj=off}}. There were 876 housing units at an average density of {{convert|130.7|/sqmi|/km2|sp=us|adj=off}}. The racial makeup of the CDP was 93.1% [[White (U.S. Census)|White]], 2.3% [[African American (U.S. Census)|African American]], 1.7% [[Native Americans in the United States|American Indian]], 0.5% [[Asian (U.S. Census)|Asian]], 0.9% [[Race (United States Census)|some other race]], and 1.5% from two or more races. [[Hispanic (U.S. Census)|Hispanic]] or [[Latino (U.S. Census)|Latino]] of any race were 14.3% of the population.<ref name="Census 2010 DP">{{Cite web| url=http://factfinder.census.gov/bkmk/table/1.0/en/DEC/10_DP/DPDP1/1600000US3677805| archive-url=https://archive.today/20200212143449/http://factfinder.census.gov/bkmk/table/1.0/en/DEC/10_DP/DPDP1/1600000US3677805| url-status=dead| archive-date=2020-02-12| title=Profile of General Population and Housing Characteristics: 2010 Demographic Profile Data (DP-1): Wainscott CDP, New York| publisher=U.S. Census Bureau, American Factfinder| access-date=2013-01-10}}</ref>

There were 264 households, out of which 24.6% had children under the age of 18 living with them, 46.2% were headed by [[Marriage|married couples]] living together, 8.0% had a female householder with no husband present, and 43.9% were non-families. 33.0% of all households were made up of individuals, and 13.3% were someone living alone who was 65 years of age or older. The average household size was 2.30, and the average family size was 2.91.<ref name="Census 2010 DP"/>

In the CDP, the population was spread out, with 21.7% under the age of 18, 9.4% from 18 to 24, 20.0% from 25 to 44, 28.6% from 45 to 64, and 20.2% who were 65 years of age or older. The median age was 44.1 years. For every 100 females, there were 115.9 males. For every 100 females age 18 and over, there were 108.6 males.<ref name="Census 2010 DP"/>

For the period 2007–2011, the estimated median annual income for a household in the CDP was $82,083, and the median income for a family was $79,375. Males had a median income of $64,688 versus $79,167 for females. The [[per capita income]] for the CDP was $51,876. About 2.0% of families and 10.3% of the population were below the [[poverty line]], including 4.7% of those under age 18 and 2.3% of those age 65 or over.<ref>{{Cite web| url=http://factfinder.census.gov/bkmk/table/1.0/en/ACS/11_5YR/DP03/1600000US3677805| archive-url=https://archive.today/20200212083801/http://factfinder.census.gov/bkmk/table/1.0/en/ACS/11_5YR/DP03/1600000US3677805| url-status=dead| archive-date=2020-02-12| title=Selected Economic Characteristics: 2007-2011 American Community Survey 5-Year Estimates (DP03): Wainscott CDP, New York| publisher=U.S. Census Bureau, American Factfinder| access-date=2013-01-10}} Due to the small sample size of the community, all of the economic figures have large margins of error.</ref>

